Taraba government has relaxed the curfew it imposed in Jalingo by two hours. The curfew, which was imposed on Monday following outbreak of crisis in some part of Jalingo metropolis, was initially effective from 4pm to 6am. The curfew, according to the Deputy Press Secretary to Governor Darius Ishaku, Mr Iliya Bikyu, was reviewed and will now be effective from 6pm to 6am instead of 4pm to 6am. He said security agencies had been directed to ensure strict compliance of the curfew. Taraba relaxes curfew as Emir calls for calm Curfew as fresh crisis erupts in Jalingo Taraba govt imposes curfew on Jalingo over fresh outbreak of crisis Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin